  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the best online coding schools available?",
  "response": "There are several highly regarded online coding schools available that cater to a variety of skill levels and interests. Some of the best online coding schools include:\n\n1. **Codecademy**: Known for its interactive learning platform, Codecademy offers courses in various programming languages like Python, JavaScript, and HTML/CSS. It provides hands-on practice and instant feedback.\n\n2. **Coursera**: Offers courses from renowned universities and institutions, such as Stanford and the University of Michigan. Coursera provides comprehensive programs in computer science and coding, including specializations and degrees.\n\n3. **Udacity**: Known for its \"Nanodegree\" programs, Udacity offers immersive, project-based learning experiences in various fields, including artificial intelligence, data science, and web development.\n\n4. **edX**: Similar to Coursera, edX offers courses from top universities including MIT and Harvard. It provides a wide range of programming and computer science courses.\n\n5. **Treehouse**: Treehouse focuses on web development, programming, and design. It offers a structured curriculum that includes coding challenges and quizzes.\n\n6. **freeCodeCamp**: This platform offers a free, comprehensive curriculum that covers web development, data visualization, and more. Users can work on real projects for nonprofits to build their portfolios.\n\n7. **Le Wagon**: Known for its intensive bootcamps, Le Wagon offers web development and data science bootcamps that aim to turn beginners into proficient developers in a short period.\n\n8. **General Assembly**: Offers various coding bootcamps and part-time courses in software engineering, data science, and more, catering to both beginners and advanced learners.\n\n9. **Khan Academy**: Provides free courses in computer programming, including JavaScript, HTML/CSS, and SQL. It\u2019s great for beginners who want a solid foundation.\n\n10. **Pluralsight**: Offers a wide range of courses on various topics including software development, IT operations, and data. It\u2019s known for its extensive library and expert-led courses.\n\nThese platforms cater to different learning styles and needs, so it's important to choose one that aligns with your goals, whether it's gaining foundational knowledge, advancing existing skills, or pursuing a career change.",
